body.name: Club Car DS "STAPLE ON" Golf Cart Seat Cover With Matching Rear Facing Seat Cover (2 Stripe)

byLineInfo.name: Visit the Up To Par Covers Store

features: MADE IN U.S.A - All our products are proudly made in U.S.A and are made with high quality marine grade vinyl and top stitched for extra strength and to help prevent water from getting through. All our products are made to order. We politely ask for up to 5 business days to produce and ship.
Free samples of our colors are available by request. Just let us know what colors you would like to see. The colors on your screen may differ from what you actually receive.

This seat cover is designed specifically for the model cart listed in the title and in the pictures of this listing. They are designed to fit the original unaltered seating. If your cart does not match the title or pictures, it will not fit your seating. If you do not see your cart here, we have plenty of other options in our store. Click on our logo to see more options. You may also contact us and send pictures of your cart to help verify what you may need.

DIY - Easy to Install - This is a full replacement seat cover. They are designed to be stapled on. There will be enough material to wrap under the seat and staple. Mostly all pictures you see of our products are all customer done and a lot of our customers have zero to very little experience in upholstery work.
When your cart is complete. Please help us by reviewing the product. Send us pictures of your work. We love to see our products on your cart.
body.description: What is included in this product - Staple On cover for front seat (Seat Portion). - Staple On Cover for front seat (Backrest Portion). - Staple On cover for rear seat (Seat Portion) - Satple On cover for rear seat (Backrest Portion) - Instructions will be included.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality and easy to install
reviews.reviewText: We wanted to renew our golf cart this past winter. It had older seat covers that had gotten dirty and did not look good any longer. Purchased these seat covers having never done anything like this so a bit apprehensive about installing them on the seats. We have the back seat also so we had to do two seats and back rests. The color is beautiful and the stitching is excellent. As far as ease of installing we had no trouble at all. You first have to remove your old covers and remove all the staples from the boards. Then you install the new covers over the cushion and pull them tight. Once you get it positioned correctly you use your stapler to fasten them. I used a 3M heavy duty fastener/stapler to attach them and it quickly and easy. If you take your time and think it through it is a very easy replacement. Our cart looks much much better now.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars great product, super hard to mold to seat curves
reviews.reviewText: First off I have upholstered several peices of furniture in the past and with great success and felt confident this project would go smoothly. package was delivered much smaller than anticipated in a plastic bag envelope. made very well I was impressed with the quality, I ordered matching covers for the back seat and all 4 peices were marked but you had to look around for it. I quickly found that my skill set was not up to the task. I was very dissappointed. so I have to pay to get it done but thats not their fault so I give 5 stars to them and 1 to me

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Our new seat covers improved the overall looks!
reviews.reviewText: Excellent quality for price, easy to install. Use stainless steel staples and be sure to wrap foam with multiple layers of clear plastic sandwich wrap to reduce opportunity of foam becoming wet before installing seat covers. Changed the entire look of golf cart. Very pleased with the end result. Good directions on proper installation found on YouTube.
